WEBVTT

00:04.994 --> 00:06.216
Hey, this is Stephen Furtick.

00:06.256 --> 00:09.340
I'm the pastor of Elevation Church, and this is our podcast.

00:09.480 --> 00:13.726
Be sure to subscribe so we can get you these new sermons every week.

00:14.006 --> 00:14.928
Hope you're blessed today.

00:21.076 --> 00:26.784
So over in the book of Revelation chapter two, verse two through five, there's a challenge.

00:26.824 --> 00:31.010
And I'm going to try to be disciplined as I preach this one.

00:31.050 --> 00:34.194
I got a little, I got a little bit off my plan at the last one.

00:35.298 --> 00:37.922
This one I'm gonna try to just stay right, right there and preach it.

00:38.342 --> 00:42.207
And because there's so much there that I believe will help you.

00:42.227 --> 00:49.397
But let's turn our attention now to the text, the angel at the church in Ephesus is receiving a message.

00:51.240 --> 01:04.498
And the word of the Lord comes, I know your works, verse two, your toil and your patient endurance and how you cannot bear with those who are evil, but have tested those who call themselves apostles and are not.

01:05.314 --> 01:06.676
found them to be false.

01:08.159 --> 01:15.331
I know you're enduring patiently and bearing up for my namesake and you have not grown weary.

01:15.371 --> 01:21.381
You're doing a lot of things right and I see it and I see you struggling and I see you showing up.

01:21.842 --> 01:26.891
But I have this against you.

01:28.994 --> 01:30.797
There's something that's working against you.

01:30.837 --> 01:31.218
There's

01:32.450 --> 01:34.734
There's something that I need to challenge you on today.

01:34.874 --> 01:40.723
I have this against you that you have abandoned the love that you had at first.

01:42.546 --> 01:46.311
Remember, therefore, from where you have fallen.

01:47.413 --> 01:47.954
Repent.

01:49.276 --> 01:50.638
It means to change your mind.

01:52.020 --> 01:53.543
It means to change your direction.

01:54.524 --> 01:54.985
Repent.

01:55.746 --> 01:58.130
Therefore, repent.

01:58.651 --> 02:00.914
Remember and repent.

02:01.570 --> 02:04.233
And do the works you did it first.

02:05.254 --> 02:12.062
If not, I will come to you and remove your lampstand from its place unless you repent.

02:13.764 --> 02:14.285
I see you.

02:14.305 --> 02:16.207
I love you.

02:18.309 --> 02:22.915
But if you don't remember and repent, you're going to lose your place.

02:24.316 --> 02:26.158
So I want to preach to you today on the subject.

02:26.819 --> 02:29.362
Put your passion in its place.

02:32.738 --> 02:38.284
And I want you to pray with me that I could communicate this message in a powerful and clear way.

02:38.464 --> 02:40.687
Father, anoint your word and open our hearts.

02:40.767 --> 02:42.068
May we hear it and do it.

02:42.729 --> 02:43.510
Never be the same.

02:43.550 --> 02:47.954
We declare it and thank you in advance for feeding us from your hand in Jesus' name.

02:48.735 --> 02:49.116
Amen.

02:49.556 --> 02:52.039
On your way to your seat touch somebody, say, you're going to get it back today.

02:52.059 --> 02:52.760
You're going to get it back.

02:52.780 --> 02:53.440
You're going to get it back.

02:54.221 --> 02:56.284
I'm just telling you right now you're going to get it back today.

02:59.187 --> 03:02.290
Hey, so bring out my props and put my little picture up.

03:03.394 --> 03:04.996
I want to show you something from last summer.

03:05.016 --> 03:11.466
I took my kids back to my hometown and took them on a tour of Monk's Corner, South Carolina.

03:12.268 --> 03:18.557
A lot of people want to go to the Holy Land and then some people on their bucket list, they just want to see Monk's Corner.

03:20.360 --> 03:26.690
So I took my kids to all of the sites that I could think of that were memorable to me growing up very proud of my small town heritage.

03:27.711 --> 03:29.814
And very proud of the church I grew up in.

03:29.834 --> 03:32.178
I took them by Monk's Corner United Methodist Church.

03:33.186 --> 03:37.431
A lady who recognized me saw us pull up, she said, little Stevie Furtick.

03:40.635 --> 03:49.506
Her sister taught my Sunday school class, and she knew I was pastoring now, proud of me and all that, said we could walk in and do whatever we wanted, she was there cleaning in.

03:50.407 --> 04:02.322
We went over to the choir room, and I showed the kids how I used to suit up on Sunday mornings when I was about, what was it, 10 mom, 11, and I was an acolyte.

04:03.042 --> 04:04.203
at the Methodist Church.

04:05.164 --> 04:06.506
And so I kind of walked them through.

04:06.526 --> 04:14.575
I wanted to show them how I did it back in the day, because not just anybody could be an acolyte.

04:14.595 --> 04:17.158
It took a special, talented kid.

04:17.178 --> 04:19.260
Very spiritually elite children were called upon it.

04:21.183 --> 04:22.664
They didn't let you light your own wick.

04:22.684 --> 04:24.086
They had a committee member for that.

04:26.629 --> 04:27.630
But I walked them through it.

04:28.070 --> 04:31.314
And so that's me at the front of the church there showing them

04:31.682 --> 04:34.686
how I used to do it, and you had to do it a certain way.

04:34.766 --> 04:40.353
You come down during the first song, and I don't remember it exactly.

04:40.373 --> 04:48.883
It's been a while, but there was a certain way you did the candles and all of that, and then you light it.

04:50.966 --> 04:51.546
It's been a while.

04:51.687 --> 04:53.989
Abby had a funny line when I was showing her all this.

04:54.090 --> 04:57.714
She said, Daddy, did you have to practice that?

04:59.714 --> 05:02.737
I said, yeah, baby, you took a lot of practice and do it just right.

05:02.757 --> 05:04.679
I can't mess it up.

05:04.699 --> 05:08.683
And plus Melissa Heidrick was sitting up there in the balcony, and I had a crush on her.

05:08.743 --> 05:15.290
And I didn't want to burn down the church in front of my childhood crush, like my robe on fire in front of my crush.

05:15.310 --> 05:16.611
So you had to practice that.

05:17.552 --> 05:27.442
And then at the end, how you put the fire out, that's important there at the end.

05:28.962 --> 05:35.729
And while I'm standing up there with them, it's memories, you know, because sometimes you go back and you just, you remember things.

05:36.430 --> 05:38.812
That was where I preached my first sermon on Youth Sunday.

05:38.932 --> 05:42.476
Now, they only give you 12 minutes to preach in the Methodist church.

05:43.577 --> 05:47.000
And I know what some of you are thinking, can we make this a Methodist church?

05:47.020 --> 05:48.261
That sounds awesome.

05:50.404 --> 05:52.165
It takes me 12 minutes to tell you hello.

05:52.666 --> 05:56.850
How many of you are glad I preached long sermons because you know you're jazzed up.

05:57.378 --> 06:01.202
This will take me a whole lot more than 12 minutes to straighten you out.

06:02.323 --> 06:02.584
Weirdo.

06:05.147 --> 06:07.209
Touch somebody, say it's going to take more than 12.

06:07.269 --> 06:08.670
You're a mess.

06:11.013 --> 06:11.434
Me too.

06:13.035 --> 06:15.258
Anyway, I was remembering that first sermon.

06:15.298 --> 06:17.460
I was preaching on Peter walking on water.

06:18.381 --> 06:22.706
And I didn't even need the full 12 minutes, to be honest with you.

06:23.298 --> 06:28.165
Within five minutes, I had used all my notes, and there were seven minutes left.

06:28.185 --> 06:29.467
I had nothing more to say.

06:29.487 --> 06:31.591
Because I was 16.

06:31.671 --> 06:32.853
I didn't have content.

06:32.873 --> 06:44.831
I was preaching on the storms of life, 16 years old, trying to tell 73-year-old Methodist women about the storms of life.

06:45.612 --> 06:48.136
I didn't have a lot of life experience, but I'll tell you what I had.

06:48.537 --> 06:52.082
I had passion.

06:52.258 --> 07:04.431
I mean, if I could have walked across the pews, I would have walked across the pews to show them how Peter came out to Jesus on that boat, and I didn't have much, much sense, but I had passion.

07:04.832 --> 07:08.856
In fact, they brought up a group of people last night when I was preaching.

07:09.236 --> 07:18.066
They had people up who have been in the church 10 years, and it made me remember back to all the things that we have now as a church that we did not have.

07:18.274 --> 07:27.842
10 years ago when we started, we didn't have all these lights and cameras for video and all this money to start campuses.

07:28.183 --> 07:30.044
God knows we didn't have a building.

07:30.765 --> 07:36.830
Our first capital campaign, you remember Greg Weinberger, I didn't have a building, a blueprint to show the people.

07:37.130 --> 07:39.673
We didn't have any of that, but we had passion.

07:40.413 --> 07:42.155
Oh, man, we had passion.

07:42.555 --> 07:45.518
We had the kind of passion that they were calling us a cult.

07:45.918 --> 07:48.260
Until they're calling you a cult, you ain't doing nothing.

07:48.240 --> 07:49.602
We had passion.

07:50.303 --> 07:52.527
I had passion preaching in that senior center.

07:53.088 --> 07:57.855
I wish I could tell him, Josh, remember you wrote me that letter the other day about my first green room.

07:57.896 --> 07:58.737
It wasn't the green room.

07:59.057 --> 07:59.959
It was a closet.

08:00.400 --> 08:01.261
It was a closet.

08:01.281 --> 08:06.890
We would move the plants out the closet, and you would knock on it with one minute left so I'd come out and leave the music.

08:06.910 --> 08:09.735
We didn't even have that many people, but we had passion.

08:10.356 --> 08:14.322
How many know you can push through a lot when you have passion?

08:18.178 --> 08:20.180
When you have passion, passion matters.

08:20.381 --> 08:32.374
I was standing there with my kids and thinking about when I started preaching and having conversations with my young self and checking my passion because in Revelation chapter 2 there is a challenge to passion.

08:32.755 --> 08:39.262
I think it's good every once in a while to challenge your passion level in contrast to the passion that you had.

08:39.322 --> 08:42.226
Do you still have passion?

08:43.828 --> 08:45.970
You remember the first apartment?

08:46.530 --> 08:47.752
that we lived in together.

08:47.812 --> 08:49.355
Holly, you remember it well.

08:50.497 --> 08:51.899
You remember the mouse traps.

08:53.943 --> 08:54.864
You remember it well.

08:54.965 --> 09:04.521
You remember how you cooked all that fried rice and pasta and made me fat within a year and a half of being your husband.

09:04.541 --> 09:06.585
I think you were trying to make sure I stayed with you.

09:06.625 --> 09:09.650
She got me so fat that first year.

09:09.858 --> 09:10.599
cooking for me.

09:10.739 --> 09:12.422
I found a picture the other day.

09:12.462 --> 09:13.524
In fact, she brought it to me.

09:13.544 --> 09:16.008
I don't know if she's trying to keep me motivated to stay in the gym.

09:16.830 --> 09:19.634
But I was about 45 pounds heavier, bro.

09:20.015 --> 09:21.337
Not in the biceps.

09:21.698 --> 09:23.481
This picture, I wish you could see this picture.

09:23.501 --> 09:27.026
I thought about putting it on the screen, but some of y'all are going to lunch after this.

09:27.047 --> 09:28.950
I don't want to mess up your lunch.

09:28.970 --> 09:36.402
And I'm standing there, got my eyes closed and my shirt off and my belly out looking like an infomercial before picture.

09:39.234 --> 09:42.959
that little apartment, Juniper Terrace Apartments, C-15.

09:43.921 --> 09:47.506
It was very small, and the insulation in the walls was very thin.

09:47.826 --> 10:01.365
And the reason I know, because Tammy from Juniper Terrace Apartments, C-16 came over to us after our first night in the apartment and knocked on the door and said, I'm your neighbor Tammy, and I just want to let you know we can hear everything.

10:01.665 --> 10:02.526
It was a duplex.

10:02.887 --> 10:07.954
I just want you to know we can hear everything that happens in C-15.

10:08.258 --> 10:29.619
And I mean everything, because we didn't have a lot of space, but we had a lot of passion, which brings us to Revelation chapter 2.

10:31.101 --> 10:32.863
This is the connection of obvious people.

10:34.484 --> 10:36.146
He said, you had something

10:36.354 --> 10:40.360
when you were small, that you lost now, that you're significant.

10:41.662 --> 10:51.316
Ephesus was not an imaginary place, so when the book of Revelation is issuing seven letters to seven churches, there are real churches with real people, with real histories.

10:52.398 --> 11:06.098
It's been 43 years since Paul started this church, traveling inland with a group of compadres that are spreading the gospel of Jesus Christ that he spends a couple of years with these people

11:06.242 --> 11:09.408
in Ephesus, and when he started out, he just met some people.

11:09.809 --> 11:16.743
There were 12 guys who were disciples of John the Baptist, and Paul asked them, do you have the Holy Spirit?

11:16.784 --> 11:19.730
They said, we don't even know that there is a Holy Spirit.

11:19.770 --> 11:22.896
They didn't have a lot of theological knowledge, but you know what they had?

11:23.177 --> 11:24.078
They had passion.

11:25.201 --> 11:27.826
Paul laid his hands on him, and when he did, they started

11:27.938 --> 11:44.601
to speak in tongues, and they received the Holy Spirit, and they didn't just speak in another language, they started speaking about Jesus, they were speaking in the synagogues, and their passion was so strong that the crowds started coming out, and then they didn't like it, because sometimes when you get passionate, apathetic people get threatened.

11:44.621 --> 11:53.874
And the Jewish religious system was not a fan of the prevalence of the gospel, so they kick Paul out of the synagogue,

11:53.986 --> 11:57.063
But how many know when you have passion, you'll find another place.

11:57.667 --> 12:01.106
Nobody can shut you down when you have real passion.

12:01.474 --> 12:04.096
If they kick you out the synagogue, you'll go to the lecture hall.

12:04.417 --> 12:06.038
And that's exactly what Paul did.

12:06.378 --> 12:08.480
And he preached powerfully in Ephesus.

12:09.021 --> 12:15.887
And it wasn't just an accident that he ended up in Ephesus.

12:15.947 --> 12:21.271
God strategically placed Paul in Ephesus because there were 300,000 people who lived there.

12:21.631 --> 12:26.436
Fourth largest city in the world at that time, known as the seventh wonder of the world.

12:26.736 --> 12:29.438
Home of the temple of Artemis, daughter of Zeus.

12:29.458 --> 12:31.460
I mean, Ephesus was a place where

12:31.440 --> 12:33.422
where people would come to get their shipments.

12:33.462 --> 12:34.403
It was a port city.

12:34.723 --> 12:35.924
It was well situated.

12:36.225 --> 12:37.446
It was an important place.

12:37.926 --> 12:39.948
So Paul is passionate.

12:40.469 --> 12:42.711
And Ephesus is an important place.

12:43.251 --> 12:47.436
And God says, I've got to get the guy with the passion in the right place.

12:47.976 --> 12:58.226
When I look back over my life, I'm grateful that God has directed my past and made sure that my passion had a place to operate.

12:58.466 --> 13:05.196
I'm grateful that God found me as a teenager and gave me a place to preach because God saw I had a passion.

13:05.597 --> 13:12.287
Now, as a parent, I'm always trying to look and make sure that if my kids have a passion, I encourage it.

13:12.668 --> 13:15.332
If you're into a Rubik's Cube, I'll buy you three.

13:15.852 --> 13:21.341
If you like Minecraft, I'll tolerate and pretend to listen to you as you explain it to me.

13:21.982 --> 13:23.664
But I want you to have a passion.

13:24.025 --> 13:27.410
Passion matters.

13:30.914 --> 13:31.695
It matters.

13:33.437 --> 13:37.162
No matter what position you're in, passion matters.

13:38.023 --> 13:43.350
And if you can't do it with passion in a small place, why in the world would God promote you to a bigger one?

13:46.354 --> 13:48.517
Paul didn't start an emphasis, but he ended up there.

13:49.058 --> 13:55.146
He started in Damascus spending time in isolation, but the same passion that was developing in his isolation.

13:56.428 --> 13:58.130
Did that make you think of David when I said that?

13:58.882 --> 14:02.788
Because that would be a great Old Testament illustration of this New Testament personality.

14:04.010 --> 14:11.200
David is a shepherd, killing lions, killing bears, and didn't even know he was preparing for Goliath.

14:11.240 --> 14:16.488
But it was the same passion in the pasture that got him to the palace.

14:16.708 --> 14:19.713
Same passion waiting for a place to happen.

14:20.995 --> 14:26.002
And that's one of the frustrating things is that you can have the right passion in the wrong place.

14:28.226 --> 14:30.849
You can have more passion than opportunity to express it.

14:31.770 --> 14:32.471
It's frustrating.

14:34.793 --> 14:36.615
I know some of you who come to church here.

14:38.537 --> 14:44.123
Some of you would express yourself more in church, but you don't know if it's appropriate.

14:44.564 --> 14:49.269
I have one friend who grew up in churches where it was more demonstrative.

14:49.289 --> 14:52.332
He said when he first came to elevation, it was kind of hard for him.

14:52.392 --> 14:52.892
I said, really?

14:53.333 --> 14:58.098
He said, yeah, because I would want to stand up while you were preaching and shout you down.

14:58.722 --> 15:00.805
There's a black guy, by the way, okay, incidentally.

15:01.887 --> 15:07.035
He said, but I was around a bunch of white people and God bless them and we all have different personalities.

15:08.016 --> 15:10.780
But I stood up when I was stand up, I was the only one.

15:10.901 --> 15:13.545
I was stand up and I was expecting everybody else to be standing to.

15:13.825 --> 15:20.776
He said, because you were preaching so passionately, the word just got in me and I couldn't stay seated and I'm standing up, but I'm the only one.

15:20.816 --> 15:27.666
All these people around me, you know, sometimes you can let other people

15:28.514 --> 15:34.623
minimize your passion and downplay your passion to the level of other people.

15:36.506 --> 15:40.612
Don't ever let another person become the ceiling on your passion.

15:41.794 --> 15:44.458
I'd rather change people than lose passion.

15:44.898 --> 15:50.226
I'd rather get some new friends that want to serve God and want to love God.

15:50.722 --> 15:55.530
I'd rather move seats than stay in my seat when the Spirit of God hit me.

15:55.550 --> 16:14.183
In fact, if you're sitting at a campus and nobody around you looks excited, raise your hand and ask the answers and they'll move your seating assignment because I need some room to praise God because when I think of the goodness of Jesus, come on, anybody got passion.

16:14.203 --> 16:15.826
And see, when you have passion,

16:15.938 --> 16:21.365
Sometimes when you get around complacing people or people who have a different personality, you feel funny.

16:21.626 --> 16:24.049
Touch somebody and say, keep your passion in his place.

16:25.931 --> 16:26.272
Right.

16:28.315 --> 16:30.317
Place for sexes in the marriage bag.

16:31.439 --> 16:38.408
I know you got passion, but passion needs a place to operate like a fire.

16:39.289 --> 16:43.796
If you're in disagreement with what I just said, let me prove it using natural elements.

16:44.236 --> 16:45.618
When I started this sermon,

16:45.922 --> 16:48.745
I lit this wick, and none of you had a problem.

16:48.765 --> 16:49.126
Why?

16:49.666 --> 16:52.550
Because it was in its proper place.

16:53.691 --> 17:05.244
But I bet if I brought this wick down to the crowd and put this fire in your hair, you say, I got it, preacher.

17:05.745 --> 17:08.188
Keep it in its place.

17:10.791 --> 17:13.714
Misplace passion is very dangerous.

17:16.450 --> 17:17.451
misplaced passion.

17:17.471 --> 17:23.659
You know, it's even more dangerous to let somebody with Brooklyn passion get around somebody with a South Charlotte attitude.

17:23.719 --> 17:25.641
What I'm trying to say is, I mean, I love my city.

17:25.661 --> 17:26.402
We're a great city.

17:26.462 --> 17:35.894
I'm not saying we owe anything to those Yankees, but I'm saying that sometimes a new person will come into the church and they're excited.

17:36.434 --> 17:37.656
I mean, they are fired up.

17:37.696 --> 17:42.802
They got a passion and let them get around Bobby, who's been a Christian for 23 years.

17:43.266 --> 17:46.189
And Bobby's looking at him saying, you don't do that around here.

17:46.550 --> 17:52.416
See, because people who are new to the faith, people who have that first love, they don't know that you're not supposed to read your Bible yet.

17:53.417 --> 17:57.221
They don't know that we only listen to it on Sundays and we don't bother with it during the week.

17:58.022 --> 18:03.648
So if you don't watch them, they'll bring that passion into your church if they don't get around.

18:08.553 --> 18:09.394
Around people.

18:11.234 --> 18:18.704
And something's happening in Ephesus because when they first started, they didn't have the knowledge, but they had the passion.

18:18.724 --> 18:21.748
They didn't have the people, but they had the passion.

18:24.251 --> 18:29.337
They didn't have the political support of the government.

18:30.058 --> 18:34.064
They didn't have a 501c3 nonprofit tax exempt status.

18:35.345 --> 18:39.090
They didn't have a Christian president, but they had passion.

18:40.610 --> 18:42.692
They had false doctrine coming into the church.

18:42.752 --> 18:52.822
In fact, Paul told Timothy one time he said, hey, I want you to look at this in 1 Timothy 1, 3, because Timothy was a young man, and he didn't have much experience.

18:53.803 --> 18:57.086
The Bible gives us reason to believe that Timothy had a timid personality.

18:57.146 --> 19:01.810
Paul had to remind him over and over again, hey, God didn't give you a spirit of timidity.

19:02.491 --> 19:09.618
Timmy is pastor in a big city church.

19:10.146 --> 19:12.069
And there's people teaching false doctrine.

19:12.930 --> 19:15.555
And there's people trying to deny the gospel of Christ.

19:16.396 --> 19:18.920
And Timothy in his twenties with the timid personality.

19:19.221 --> 19:22.105
By the way, passion is not a personality type.

19:24.890 --> 19:26.753
Passion isn't how high you jump.

19:28.435 --> 19:31.360
Passion is how straight you walk when your feet hit the ground.

19:33.824 --> 19:34.485
Put this down.

19:35.647 --> 19:37.490
If you're passionate, you take notes in church.

19:40.322 --> 19:42.305
The proof of passion is perseverance.

19:43.947 --> 19:45.349
I'll prove it to you in the Scripture.

19:46.430 --> 19:48.493
I'll prove it to you from 1 Timothy 1, 3.

19:48.774 --> 19:56.444
Paul says, Timothy, I urged you before when I was on my way through Macedonia, and I'm telling you again, remain in ethicists.

19:56.464 --> 19:56.945
Now watch this.

19:57.285 --> 19:59.789
You don't have to tell somebody to stay somewhere they want to be.

20:01.311 --> 20:04.375
I've never had a massage therapist have to tell me to stay on the table.

20:06.317 --> 20:09.682
I have had a physical trainer have to tell me to do another rep.

20:10.658 --> 20:12.099
to urge me to keep going.

20:12.139 --> 20:15.382
You don't urge people to do something they naturally want to do.

20:15.743 --> 20:18.646
So there must have been an instinct in Timothy to run.

20:18.946 --> 20:19.486
You're young.

20:19.707 --> 20:20.848
You're inexperienced.

20:21.468 --> 20:23.650
There's false doctrine circulating in the church.

20:24.051 --> 20:26.453
Timothy must not have been feeling it anymore.

20:28.215 --> 20:30.016
Timothy's fire might have been going out.

